        />
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Project Header -->
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-8 md:px-16 pb-16">
      <h1 class="text-h2 font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-4">
        Boulder Box Saigon - Vietnam's First Boutique Bouldering Concept
      </h1>
      <p class="text-body text-white/60">
        Business Owner, Product Management, Business Management
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- About The Project -->
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-8 md:px-16 pb-16 grid md:grid-cols-[300px_1fr] gap-8 md:gap-16">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-nav font-heading font-semibold text-primary mb-4">About The Project</h3>
      </div>
      
      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6">
        <div class="space-y-2 text-body">
          <p><strong>Role:</strong> Founder & Business Development Head</p>
          <p><strong>Platform:</strong> Physical Facility + Community-driven Experience</p>
          <p><strong>Duration:</strong> August 2023 - Current</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-t border-white/10 my-8"></div>

        <h3 class="text-[24px] font-heading font-bold text-white">Project Overview</h3>
        <p class="text-body text-white/80 leading-relaxed">
          <strong>Boulder Box Saigon</strong> was born out of a personal passion for climbing and a clear market opportunity: the lack of accessible, high-quality bouldering spaces in Vietnam. As both <strong>Founder and Business Development Head</strong>, I led the entire venture - from market research and construction to branding, team-building, and business growth.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body text-white/80 leading-relaxed">
          The goal was to <strong>introduce a new concept of home-scale bouldering gyms</strong> tailored to urban lifestyles, while fostering a tight-knit climbing community. With no blueprint to follow in the local context, the project demanded not only creative thinking and operational rigor, but also cultural adaptation and deep customer empathy.
        </p>

        <img 
          src="https://framerusercontent.com/images/WP4CqbcYZRbpVo0Ka8Au5OOod6E.png?width=7008&height=4120" 
          alt="Boulder Box Saigon Overview"
          class="w-full rounded-lg my-8"
        />

        <h3 class="text-[24px] font-heading font-bold text-white">Objectives</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-3 text-body text-white/80">
          <li>Launch a boutique bouldering facility that brings <strong>sport climbing into the urban home and lifestyle space</strong>.</li>
          <li>Build a <strong>community-centered climbing culture</strong> in Ho Chi Minh City.</li>
          <li>Drive sustainable growth through <strong>quality coaching</strong>, customer retention, and experiential engagement.</li>
          <li>Establish Boulder Box as <strong>a recognized local leader in Vietnam's emerging climbing scene</strong>.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-[24px] font-heading font-bold text-white mt-12">Key Challenges</h3>
        
        <h4 class="text-[20px] font-heading font-semibold text-primary mt-6">Market Unknowns</h4>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-3 text-body text-white/80">
          <li>Climbing was still <strong>a niche sport in Vietnam</strong>, with limited public facilities and low consumer familiarity.</li>
          <li>No prior local models for <strong>home bouldering gym businesses</strong>, requiring everything from scratch—market education, pricing structures, and design logic.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="text-[20px] font-heading font-semibold text-primary mt-6">Operational Demands</h4>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-3 text-body text-white/80">
          <li>Sourcing <strong>safe and durable construction materials</strong> for custom climbing walls locally was difficult.</li>
          <li>Balancing <strong>space constraints</strong> with varied route-setting styles and safety features took iterative on-site problem-solving.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="text-[20px] font-heading font-semibold text-primary mt-6">Talent Scarcity</h4>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-3 text-body text-white/80">
          <li>Vietnam had <strong>few trained climbing professionals</strong>, especially in coaching and route-setting.</li>
          <li>Required a strong focus on hiring, training, and retaining the right people to deliver consistent, high-quality experiences.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-[24px] font-heading font-bold text-white mt-12">Approach & Execution</h3>
        
        <h4 class="text-[20px] font-heading font-semibold text-white mt-8">1. Market Research & Concept Development</h4>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-3 text-body text-white/80">
          <li>Conducted a comprehensive <strong>competitive and cultural analysis</strong> of Vietnam's sports and fitness market.</li>
          <li>Identified gaps in <strong>indoor sport accessibility</strong>, growing interest in climbing, and a desire for boutique fitness experiences.</li>
          <li>Developed a unique positioning: <strong>"climbing meets lifestyle,"</strong> blending sport, design, and community.</li>
          <li>Drafted the layout design & planning, together with a 3D mockup for the construction team to follow.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-8">
          <img 
            src="https://framerusercontent.com/images/v3Cs6EI7Vtr4AGopxo8c0N4HPOE.png?width=1534&height=1086" 
            alt="Design Planning"
            class="w-full rounded-lg"
          />
